### Library
-  [@ngneat/reactive- forms](https://github.com/ngneat/reactive- forms)
  -  Type safety with formGroup
  -  Save form entries to session storage and save/load when reloaded, etc.

-  [@datorama/akita](https://github.com/datorama/akita)
  -  State management library, making code more readable when processing the results of requests asynchronously because the subscribe nesting is less deep
  -  ngOnInit to state httpRequest().subscribe() and ease the process of getting the value asynchronously from the store.
  -  Store information you want to keep when reloading, such as information on the page you are currently on, to make it easier to describe the loading process
  -  I just looked at the site and it mentioned [@ngneat/elf](https://github.com/ngneat/elf), so I`ll try it next time.

-  [ng2- adsense](https://github.com/scttcper/ng2- adsense)
  -  Angular escapes script tags, so if you implement your own, it will do what you need to do to manipulate the dom.

-  [ng- recaptcha](https://github.com/DethAriel/ng- recaptcha)
  -  A reCAPTCHA can be installed for information you do not want the bot to see, or if you want to prevent access (site keys must be created in GCP).

-  [@ng- bootstrap/ng- bootstrap](https://github.com/ng- bootstrap/ng- bootstrap)
  -  bootstrap library for Angular

-  [@compodoc/compodoc](https://github.com/compodoc/compodoc)
  -  It automatically generates documentation for Angular applications.
  -  To use it, add the following configuration file: `npx @compodoc/compodoc - p . /tsconfig.doc.json - d src/doc`.
  -  Document to be created - > [sample](https://portal.kemu.site/doc/)

`tsconfig.doc.json`.

```json
{
  "include": ["src/**/*.ts"],
  "exclude": ["src/test.ts", "src/**/*.spec.ts"]
}
```

### Code
#### Display message - > Delete after 5 seconds

```ts
import { Injectable } from '@angular/core';
import { interval } from 'rxjs';

export interface AlertMessage {
  type: string;
  body: string;
}

@Injectable({
  providedIn: 'root',
})
export class MessageService {
  constructor() {}
  private _messages: AlertMessage[] = [];

  get messages() {
    return this._messages;
  }

  pushMessage(message: AlertMessage) {
    this._messages.push(message);
    interval(5000).pipe(take(1)).subscribe((_) => this._messages.shift());
  }
}
```

#### Display loading on screen transitions

```ts
this.router.events.subscribe((event) => {
  if (event instanceof NavigationStart) {
    this.loading = true;
  } else if (
    event instanceof NavigationEnd ||
    event instanceof NavigationCancel ||
    event instanceof NavigationError
  ) {
    this.loading = false;
  }
});
```

#### Incremental Search
  -  doc: https://ng- bootstrap.github.io/#/components/typeahead/examples


```ts
{
  search: OperatorFunction<string, readonly string[]> = (text$: Observable<string>) => {
    return text$
      .pipe(debounceTime(200), distinctUntilChanged())
      .pipe(
        map((text) => Object.keys(this.searchData).filter((title) => title.toLowerCase().includes(text.toLowerCase())))
      );
  };
}
```

```html
<input
  class="form-control"
  placeholder="search"
  NgbTypeahead
  [ngbTypeahead]="search"
  (selectItem)="selectArticle($event)"
  #instance="ngbTypeahead"
  (blur)="instance.dismissPopup()"
/>
```

#### Interrupt the process before reloading

```ts
constoractor() {
  window.onbeforeunload = () => this.ngOnDestroy();
}

```

